    <!-- About -->
    <string name="about_title">About Soularium</string>
    <string name="about_what_is_heading">WHAT IS SOULARIUM?</string>
    <string name="about_what_is_body">Soularium is a set of 50 images and 5 questions that help people talk about their life and spiritual journey. People simply choose the images that describe their experiences.</string>
    <string name="about_meaningful_body">Because images connect deeply with our experiences, they enable us to engage in meaningful conversations about life and God. With Soularium you’ll discover how easy and enjoyable it is to come alongside someone on their journey.</string>
    <string name="about_50_5">Soularium: 50 images, 5 questions.</string>
    <string name="about_how_to_heading">HOW TO START A SOULARIUM CONVERSATION</string>
    <string name="about_how_to_body">There are many ways — so just do what comes naturally to you. Or try this: “Would you be willing to tell me about your spiritual journey sometime?” If your friend is interested, suggest using Soularium. Then: “I’ve found that people enjoy using photos to describe their life and spiritual experiences. Would you be willing to choose the ones that describe yours?” Show your friend Soularium.</string>
    <string name="about_tips_heading">HELPFUL TIPS</string>
    <string name="about_tip_listening_title">1. Soularium is about LISTENING.</string>
    <string name="about_tip_listening_body">Allow people time to select images. Actively listen as they describe their choices.</string>
    <string name="about_tip_connections_title">2. Look for connections.</string>
    <string name="about_tip_connections_body">Look for connections between their story and yours. What experiences and desires do you have in common?</string>
    <string name="about_sunlight">JUST AS SUNLIGHT ILLUMINATES A SOLARIUM, SOULARIUM OPENS A WINDOW TO THE SOUL.</string>

